==Signs and symptoms==

The key symptoms of PFAPA are those in its name: periodic high [[fever]] at intervals of about 3–5 weeks, as well as [[aphthous ulcer]]s, [[pharyngitis]] and/or [[adenitis]]. In between episodes, and even during the episodes, the children appear healthy. At least 6 months of episodes. Diagnosis requires recurrent negative throat cultures and that other causes (such as EBV, CMV, FMF) be excluded.<ref name="SarahLongPFAPA">{{cite journal
